  "subject": "Add more modes to  KRD Vagrant network config",
  "commit_message": "Add more modes to  KRD Vagrant network config\n\nKRD assumes all networking interfaces of type nat.\nThis patch removes that assumption and gives user\nmore choices like routed network for vagrant\nnetwork. By default KRD assumes 10.10.10.10/24\nnetwork per VM and is provided in the config file.\nWith this patch the name of network as krd is\nrequired.\nExamples in cofig/samples in this patch. In file\nconfig/samples/pdf.yml.mini shows example of\nadding new networks in subset of VM's.\n\nChange-Id: Ib518277b0862af02b0476aa377222ecfdb4f3fc0\nSigned-off-by: Ritu Sood <ritu.sood@intel.com>\nIssue-ID: MULTICLOUD-301\n",
